He frowned.\
\'93I am back,\'94 he said hotly, \'93why do you not cheer?\'94\
They opened their mouths, but the cheers would not come. He overlooked it in his haste to tell the glorious tidings.\
\'93Great news, boys,\'94 he cried, \'93I have brought at last a mother for you all.\'94\
