\'93Tut, tut, tut,\'94 he said, \'93where does she lie?\'94\
\'93In yonder glade.\'94\
\'93I will put a glass thing in her mouth,\'94 said Slightly, and he made-believe to do it, while Peter waited. It was an anxious moment when the glass thing was withdrawn.\
\'93How is she?\'94 inquired Peter.\
\'93Tut, tut, tut,\'94 said Slightly, \'93this has cured her.\'94\
\'93I am glad!\'94 Peter cried.\
\'93I will call again in the evening,\'94 Slightly said; \'93give her beef tea out of a cup with a spout to it;\'94 but after he had returned the hat to John he blew big breaths, which was his habit on escaping from a difficulty.\
