At that they fell on their knees. \'93No, no!\'94 they cried so piteously that every pirate smiled.\
\'93Fetch the cat, Jukes,\'94 said Hook; \'93it\'92s in the cabin.\'94\
The cabin! Peter was in the cabin! The children gazed at each other.\
\'93Ay, ay,\'94 said Jukes blithely, and he strode into the cabin. They followed him with their eyes; they scarce knew that Hook had resumed his song, his dogs joining in with him:\
